data.name: COOKIES_MESSAGE
data.value: This site uses cookies to provide you the best experience possible. By continuing without changing your settings, we will assume you are happy to receive cookies from our site. You can change your cookie settings at any time.

data.name: COOKIES_READ_MORE_MESSAGE
data.value:
Cookies may be used on some pages of our sites. In many cases, the information we collect using cookies and other tools is only used in a non-identifiable way, without any reference to Personal Information. For example, we use information we collect about all website users to optimize our websites and to understand website traffic patterns. In some cases, we do associate the information we collect using cookies and other technology with your Personal Information. This Privacy Policy applies to the collection and use of any Personal Information that is obtained through the use of cookies and otherwise.

What is a cookie?

A cookie is a text file unique to you that is related to your computer or mobile device and it can be picked up by a server, allowing the website to pick up things such as your preferences, what is in your shopping basket or allow us to recognize you when you return. This information helps us dynamically generate web content and design web functionality specifically for users of our sites and enables us to provide you with a customized experience each time that you visit.

What types of cookie do PRGX use?

Most common technologies such as cookies, pixel tags, browser analysis tools, server logs and web beacons are used on most websites.

We may also use Flash Cookies (also known as Local Stored Objects) and similar technologies to personalize and enhance your online experience. The Adobe Flash Player is an application that allows rapid development of dynamic content, such as video clips and animation. We use Flash cookies for security purposes and to help remember settings and preferences. We do not use Flash cookies or similar technologies for behavioral or interest-based advertising purposes. To manage Flash cookies, you may visit Adobe’s website at kb2.adobe.com/cps/526/52697ee8.html or visit www.adobe.com.

Pixel tags and web beacons are tiny graphic images placed on website pages or in emails that allow us to determine whether you have performed a specific action. When you access these pages or open or click on an email, the pixel tags and web beacons generate a notice of that action. These tools allow us to measure response to our communications and improve our web pages and promotions.

How do we collect information using cookies?

We collect many different types of information from cookies and other technologies. For example, we may collect information from the device you use to access our website, your operating system type, browser type, domain, and other system settings, as well as the language your system uses and the country and time zone where your device is located. Our server logs may also record the IP address assigned to the device you are using to connect to the Internet. An IP address is a unique number that devices use to identify and communicate with each other on the Internet. We may also collect information about the website you were you visit after you leave our site.

Can cookies be disabled?

In most cases, if you prefer not to allow the use of cookies, you can manage cookie preferences and opt-out of having cookies and other data collection technologies used by adjusting the settings on your browser. All browsers are different, so please visit the “help” section of your browser to learn about the privacy settings that may be available. Please be advised that disabling cookies may result in limited functionality on our sites.

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_1
data.value:
PRGX Supplier Information Management (SIM), is an on-line network which captures key information from Suppliers, verifies that information and maintains the information for all registered Network participants; both Suppliers and Buyers.The PRGX SIM platform comprises of functionality for both Suppliers and their Customers (Buyers) as follows:For Suppliers: account set-up, questionnaire’s to capture key information, secure document management, alerts and monitoring to update information in a timely fashion, reporting of outcomes and recommendations.For Buyers: account set-up, secure access to their Suppliers’ information, outcomes of verifications conducted and a suite of risk based reporting

The PRGX SIM platform comprises of functionality for both Suppliers and their Customers (Buyers) as follows:

For Suppliers: account set-up, questionnaire’s to capture key information, secure document management, alerts and monitoring to update information in a timely fashion, reporting of outcomes and recommendations.

For Buyers: account set-up, secure access to their Suppliers’ information, outcomes of verifications conducted and a suite of risk based reporting

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_10
data.value:
Depending upon the type of questionnaire completed, you will obtain:

  • A completed assessment, meeting the needs of your Customer and viewable by them through the Network
  • Your own detailed document repository and archive of submissions, which may be made available to other Buying organisations as you see fit
  • Point by point assessment with gaps identified for you to consider – these are areas which Buying organisations review in order to support purchasing decisions
  • In the case of CIPS Sustainability Index, an industry recognised certification, with guidance and material to help you publicise your rating
  • On-going support to maintain and grow your information as a valuable Sales tool

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_11
data.value:
In the first instance, a Buying organisation is required to sign our Engagement Letter which details the scope and service to be provided.

Once an Engagement Letter is in place, any nominated and agreed Buyer user-accounts are quickly set-up by the PRGX Support team. You will be informed of your website landing page, typically reflecting your Organisation’s branding, together with your personal user-account and password.

A full service of training and adoption is available to ensure you obtain maximum value following the on-boarding of your targeted Suppliers.

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_2
data.value:
The CIPS Sustainability Index (CSI) is a Supplier sustainability assessment, which reviews a Suppliers credentials in the areas of Economic, Environmental and Social/Ethical performance. Sustainability is often a key purchasing criteria for large Buying organisations.

CSI has been developed by the Chartered Institute of Purchasing & Supply (CIPS) and through a wide industry-based consultation program and research from the University of West England. CSI is operated by PRGX and is available to access either directly via the CSI website www.CIPS-sustainanbility-index.com, or through the PRGX SIM network.

PRGX SIM therefore provides Buyers and their Suppliers a capability to maintain key Supplier information together with detailed sustainability credentials all in one place.

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_3
data.value:
For Buyers it is increasingly important to understand, assess and monitor a wide range of credentials of their Suppliers. This is driven both by regulatory requirements, the end-consumer and a greater appreciation internally of supply chain and third party risks. As a result, buying organisations routinely ask Suppliers to complete their own detailed assessments at considerable time and effort to both parties.

PRGX SIM offers a single point of registration and assessment for many of the commonly asked questions from Buyers of their Suppliers; covering areas of financial risk, sustainability commitments, health & safety and data security policies.

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_4
data.value:
By registering and completing your assessments in a timely fashion, the Supplier is meeting the necessary compliance objectives of the Buyer. These objectives are a condition of business and important to the risk management of the Buyer.

For the Supplier time and cost is saved through a single place of registration that you may request/approve other Buying organisations to access. Also, ongoing, Suppliers are monitored and prompted to ensure documentation is kept maintained (such as expiring certificates), making the Network an invaluable tool for Suppliers to maintain their own credentials in one place for the benefit of their own internal teams.

Additionally, both Buyer and Supplier participants receive detailed assessments of their risk profile and where appropriate recommendations for practical improvements. For Suppliers undertaking the CSI assessment there is the additional benefit of a CIPS based rating and certification which may be widely used to publicise your sustainability credentials.

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_5
data.value:
Suppliers are invited to the system by a participating existing Customer (ie Buyer) or prospective Buyer who wishes to understand and verify your credentials.

The Supplier is sent an invitation request by the PRGX Supplier Engagement team on behalf of the Buyer. This communication, either by letter and/or e-mail, will contain the website for access and any specific instructions for the type of information required.

Access is simple and straightforward. An on-line user-account is initially created, which just takes a few minutes. After that, the Supplier can complete their Company Registration which includes submitting summary profile data, such as Address and Contacts. Typically the entire process takes just 15 minutes.

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_6
data.value:
Obtaining a user-account and completing your Registration is free. You may Register and obtain the benefit of your profile being viewable by any of the Buying organisations who are registered to the PRGX Network.

After completing your Registration, you will be provided access to a personalised Home Page which will identify the questionnaire’s you are required to complete. Mandatory questionnaires, requiring your immediate attention, will have a red highlight.

Each questionnaire is clearly labelled with an individual fee, with prices beginning from just £99. The fee is in respect of our work in reviewing the submission, completing associated verifications and maintaining the information annually.

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_7
data.value:
Questionnaires can be part-completed, saved and worked-on over a period of time to ensure a correct submission.

When you are ready to submit, simply check-out using the on-line shopping basket. Several questionnaires may be completed together, and you can check-out at one time and make one payment.

Also making payment is easy. We use a Secure third party credit/debit card processing system. A full account history and electronic invoices are maintained for your records and can be downloaded from the system.

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_8
data.value:
This depends upon the number and type of questionnaires you are being requested to complete.

The standard compliance questionnaires can be completed within 30 minutes if you have the necessary certificates to hand. The questionnaire forms are easy to navigate and it is fast and simple to upload required documentation.

Completing the CIPS Sustainability Index (CSI) assessment will take slightly longer due to the greater depth and range of evidences required. However each question is accompanied by help texts to aid your progress.

There is a dedicated PRGX Support team to assist you at any time in the process.

data.name: FAQ_ANSWER_9
data.value:
Once you make payment for any particular questionnaire, you are able to press the Submit button and request the assessment to be completed.

Your completed questionnaire is then passed to the PRGX Supplier Evaluation team who will individually review each response and the evidences attached, and where possible verify the information against publically available data sources.

Your assessment is typically completed within 10 business days of submission and the result is made available to you and your requesting Buyer. You may release this information to any other Buyer in the PRGX network as you require.
